The paper discusses a technique for collaborative filtering, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes two new graphic models for collaborative filtering, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of probabilistic graphic models, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the importance of modeling user preferences and ratings, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
